Reference Documents:-
https://developer.hashicorp.com/consul/docs/manage/dns/views
https://developer.hashicorp.com/consul/docs/manage/dns/forwarding/k8s?page=k8s&page=dns&page=enable
https://developer.hashicorp.com/consul/docs/secure-mesh/certificate/permissive-mtls
https://developer.hashicorp.com/consul/docs/register/external/permissive-mtls
https://developer.hashicorp.com/consul/docs/manage/dns/views/enable

UseCase:
Establish communication between non service-mesh app static-client and service-mesh app static-server.

Create kind cluster:
kind create cluster --name=dc1

Deploy consul on K8:-
helm install consul hashicorp/consul --values=values.yaml --debug

Deploy non-mesh and mesh apps:-
kubectl apply -f static-client-non-mesh.yaml
kubectl apply -f static-server-mesh.yaml

Update coreDNS config map to add the .consul domain resolution block in it.
kubectl edit cm coredns -n kube-system   # Refer the config map attached in the folder section
kubectl rollout restart deploy coredns -n kube-system

Exec into static-client non-mesh app:-
/ # nslookup static-server.virtual.consul
Server:		10.96.0.10
Address:	10.96.0.10:53

Name:	static-server.virtual.consul
Address: 240.0.0.1

Name:	static-server.virtual.consul
Address: 240.0.0.1

/ # nslookup static-server.service.consul
Server:		10.96.0.10
Address:	10.96.0.10:53

Name:	static-server.service.consul
Address: 10.244.0.15

/ # nslookup static-server
Server:		10.96.0.10
Address:	10.96.0.10:53

** server can't find static-server.cluster.local: NXDOMAIN

** server can't find static-server.cluster.local: NXDOMAIN

Name:	static-server.default.svc.cluster.local
Address: 10.96.34.29

** server can't find static-server.svc.cluster.local: NXDOMAIN

** server can't find static-server.svc.cluster.local: NXDOMAIN

This shows that DNS resolution for .consul domain is happening successfully. But if you run curl command, it wont work because static-client is sending plain text to mesh app static-server expecting mTLS encrypted traffic. 
See below the output:-

/ # curl static-server.service.consul
curl: (52) Empty reply from server
/ # curl static-server.service.consul:8080
curl: (52) Empty reply from server
/ # curl static-server:1234
curl: (52) Empty reply from server

So inorder to make this actual communication happen using curl, we have to configure mesh service to allow permissive mTLS so that non-mesh app can talk to mesh apps.

Run:
kubectl apply -f mesh.yaml
kubectl apply -f servicedefault.yaml

Validate:-
kubectl exec -it static-client-67cd8cb9b6-hsxpb -c static-client -- sh
/ # curl static-server.service.consul:8080
"hello world from dc1"
/ # curl static-server:1234
"hello world from dc1"
/ # curl static-server
/ # curl static-server.default.svc.cluster.local:1234
"hello world from dc1"

Note: By default consul-dns-proxy service listens DNS queries on port 53, but you can customize the port for eg 5353. Refer values_5353.yaml and coreDNS-configmap_5353.yaml to see the usage.


